  "text": "Placement instability was yet another challenge for local authorities. For example, two in five looked after children for over five years had experienced more than six placements while a quarter with five years' care history had witnessed more than ten placements. The changes imply changes in carers and schools as well. Instability affected schooling and educational progress hence low performance. [CITATION_1] . Strangely, adolescents did not see changing placements as harmful to their development. (Department of Health (DoH), 2000).",
